          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Celiac disease </span></span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A patient presents with enlargement of salivary glands, fibrosis of the pancreas, and increased serum levels of IgG4. Which condition from the following list is not typically associated with the spectrum of IgG4-related disease?</span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q2160097",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 31878,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [
        5
      ],
      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ans. D) Celiac disease</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option D:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Celiac disease is <strong>not an lgG4-related disease.</strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>IgG4-related disease (IgG4-RD) </strong>is a newly recognized constellation of disorders characterized by <strong>tissue infiltrates dominated by IgG4 antibody-producing plasma cells and lymphocytes, particularly T cells, storiform fibrosis, obliterative phlebitis</strong>, and usually <strong>increased serum IgG4</strong>. IgG4-RD spectrum includes:</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Celiac disease:</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"> Celiac disease is an <strong>autoimmune </strong>condition triggered by <strong>ingestion of gluten </strong>in genetically<strong> susceptible </strong>individuals. It is <strong>not associated with IgG4-related disease</strong>, which is characterized by<strong> tissue infiltrates dominated by IgG4-positive plasma cells and lymphocytes, storiform fibrosis, and obliterative phlebitis.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Explanation:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option A: Mikulicz syndrome:</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"> Mikulicz syndrome involves <strong>enlargement and fibrosis of the salivary and lacrimal glands </strong>and is a recognized part of the<strong> IgG4-related disease spectrum</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option B: Riedel thyroiditis:</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"> Riedel thyroiditis is a<strong> fibrosing inflammatory process </strong>involving the<strong> thyroid gland</strong>, often associated with <strong>IgG4-related disease</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option C: Idiopathic retroperitoneal fibrosis:</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"> Idiopathic retroperitoneal fibrosis is characterized by <strong>fibrous tissue </strong>in the <strong>retroperitoneum and can be associated with IgG4-related disease.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Educational Objective:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>IgG4-related disease </strong>is a <strong>fibro-inflammatory </strong>condition characterized by several features, including <strong>tissue infiltration with IgG4-positive plasma cells</strong>. It <strong>does not encompass celiac disease</strong>, which has a d<strong>ifferent pathophysiology related to gluten sensitivity. </strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ref Robbins 10<sup>th</sup>/232</span></span></strong></p>",
